Your choices will produce points for both yourself and the “Other” person, and vice versa. Every point has value: the more points one receives, the better.
 

    Here’s an example:

B: you receive 500 points; the other receives 500 points  

C: you receive 550 points; the other receives 300 points 

 

So, you see that your choice influences both your points (on top) and the other's points (on bottom).
